Let $p$ be a prime and $G$ a residually finite group satisfying some non-trivial identity $f \equiv~1$. Suppose that for every $x,y \in G$ there exists a $p$-power $q=q(x,y)$ such that $[x,y^{{\varphi}}]^q = 1$. Then the derived subgroup $\nu(G)'$ is locally finite. 
\end{thmA}

